# Python3 program to add two numbers
#number1,number2,sum are variablre.
#input() is a built-in function to take user input.
#input() function always give us string type data.
number1 = input("First number: ")
number2 = input("\nSecond number: ")

# Adding two numbers
#float() function is a floating point data type.
# User might also enter float numbers
sum = float(number1) + float(number2)

# Display the sum
# will print value in float
#.format method returns the formatted string.
print("The sum of {0} and {1} is {2}" .format(number1, number2, sum))
